HEADWORD: Feticide
<hw>Fe"ti*cide</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>f⟦oe⟧ticide</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[<ets>Fetus</ets> + L.
<ets>caedere</ets> to kill.]</ety> <fld>(Med. & Law)</fld> <def>The act
of killing the fetus in the womb; the offense of procuring an
abortion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

